ABSTRACT
This project presents the design and development of a web-based Final Year Project (FYP) Management System that supports students, supervisors, and university administrators in managing project activities efficiently. The system is developed to address common challenges in traditional FYP workflows such as manual tracking, delayed communication, inconsistent supervision records, and difficulty monitoring progress.

The proposed platform centralizes key processes including user management, supervision session tracking, reminders, feedback submission, analytics, and real-time communication. In addition, it introduces intelligent features such as AI-assisted academic guidance and research paper summarization to improve student learning outcomes and advisor support.

A microservices architecture is adopted to ensure modularity, scalability, and maintainability. Core services are separated by domain (authentication, supervision, notification, reporting, and integration), while a modern web frontend provides a responsive and user-friendly interface. The system also includes data visualization components to represent project status and milestone progress.

Overall, the developed solution demonstrates that a web-based, service-oriented platform can improve transparency, collaboration, and decision-making in FYP supervision and administration.


